    public interface DumbAware
    A marker interface for the things that are allowed to run in dumb mode (when indices are in background update). Implementors must take care of handling and/or not calling non-DumbAware parts of system.

    Some known implementors are:

  • AnActions (see DumbAwareAction)
  • FileEditorProviders
  • post-startup activities (StartupActivity / StartupManager.registerPostStartupDumbAwareActivity(Runnable))
  • Stacktrace Filters
  • SelectInTargets
  • IconProviders
  • CompletionContributors
  • TextEditorHighlightingPasses
  • ToolWindowFactorys
  • MultiHostInjectors
See Also:
DumbService, DumbAwareRunnable, PossiblyDumbAware
